<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-19834] camel-test-infra-elasticsearch container start fails if ca cert is not present</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-19834</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is possible to configure elasticsearch container to not generate a self signed CA certificate by basically disabling SSL. In this case the container init would fail with &lt;tt&gt;java.util.NoSuchElementException: No value present&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this is due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/camel-4.0.x/test-infra/camel-test-infra-elasticsearch/src/test/java/org/apache/camel/test/infra/elasticsearch/services/ElasticSearchLocalContainerService.java#L99&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/camel-4.0.x/test-infra/camel-test-infra-elasticsearch/src/test/java/org/apache/camel/test/infra/elasticsearch/services/ElasticSearchLocalContainerService.java#L99&lt;/a&gt; being called even if CA cert is not present.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13549664">CAMEL-19834</key>
