                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17762079" author="JIRAUSER285918" created="Tue, 5 Sep 2023 12:59:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It has been done this way because IIRC by default the security pack is enabled and since we use the OS version of ES, we have to configure TLS/SSL. So to implement it, you will probably need to disable the security pack, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/security-settings.html#general-security-settings&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/security-settings.html#general-security-settings&lt;/a&gt; for more details&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17762083" author="valdar" created="Tue, 5 Sep 2023 13:16:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that it is wrong to call sslContext = getContainer().createSslContextFromCa(); outside the scope of .ifPresent . &lt;br/&gt;
Here there is the PR that you can review and discuss: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/11302&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/11302&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17762190" author="valdar" created="Tue, 5 Sep 2023 18:43:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix merged in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/11302&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/11302&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
